    "Extended results for CountGen [15] and ISAC.",
    "MethodIntraCompBench (Instance) (↑)#2 #3 #4 #5 Avg.SDXL [4] 90% 71% 49% 32% 61% + CountGen CVPR'25 [15] 97% 83% 52% 44% 69% + ISAC (Ours) 96% 89% 71% 47% 76% + CountGen + ISAC (Ours) 98% 91% 74% 50% 78%Among training-free layout guidance methods [22, 31-36, 38, 60], Bounded Attention [38] is the only approach that explicitly separates self-and cross-attention across box-level masks to mitigate semantic mixing.",
    "Because it only partitions semantics by boxes, it cannot guarantee instance discrimination and often fails to count correctly in crowded scenes (see Fig. 12).Moreover, its mutual-exclusivity assumption-each pixel belongs to at most one box -breaks under overlapping or tightly packed layouts.",
    "Thus, the resulting suppression of attention in shared regions degrades spatial control and semantic fidelity (Fig. 13).",
    "Since performance can also depend on the arbitrary ownership order under overlap, we exclude Bounded Attention from our layout comparisons."
